      "description": "A comprehensive survey of published hemolysis prediction studies using power-law damage models was conducted to establish that the CFD model form and parameter choices are consistent with accepted practice. Seventeen peer-reviewed publications were reviewed, covering a range of rotary blood pump geometries. The literature survey confirmed that the scalar stress-based power-law model with Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients is widely used and yields relative hemolysis index predictions within acceptable bounds for Class II CPB devices. No discrepancy with the required verification method was noted by the assessment team.",
